{"word":"λάσιος","slug":"λάσιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λάσιος</b></el> <el>(λά˘σιος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>akin to <a href='S:δασύς'><el>δασύς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>hairy, rough, shaggy, woolly</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>shaggy with brushwood, bushy</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>; <el>τὰ λάσια</el> <i>bushes</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}